Claims CLAIMS:  What is claimed is: 1. A method for treating a microelectronic substrate, comprising receiving the microelectronic substrate in a vacuum process chamber comprising a fluid expansion component; supplying, to the fluid expansion component, a fluid mixture comprising: a temperature less than 273K; and a pressure that is greater than atmospheric pressure; providing the fluid mixture to the fluid expansion component such that at least a portion of the fluid mixture will contact the microelectronic substrate, the process chamber being maintained at a chamber pressure of 35Torr or less; and maintaining a reservoir pressure in the fluid expansion component that is greater than the chamber pressure and less than the incoming pressure; maintaining an outlet pressure of the fluid expansion component that is greater than the chamber pressure and less than the reservoir pressure; and removing objects from the microelectronic substrate using the portion of the fluid mixture that contacts the microelectronic substrate. 2. The method of claim 1 , wherein the fluid mixture comprises greater than 50% by weight of the fluid mixture being in gas phase. 3. The method of claim 1 , wherein the fluid mixture comprising a gas mixture of nitrogen to argon between a 1 :1 to 1 1 :1 ratio. 4. The method of claim 1 , wherein the temperature is greater than or equal to 70K and less than or equal to 120K. 5. The method of claim 1 , wherein the process chamber is maintained at less than 10Torr. 6. The method of claim 1 , wherein the fluid mixture comprising at least a 1 :1 mixture of nitrogen or argon to one or more of the following: xenon, helium, neon, krypton or carbon dioxide. 7. The method of claim 1 , wherein the fluid mixture comprising at least a 4:1 mixture of nitrogen or argon to one or more of the following: xenon, krypton or carbon dioxide. 8. The method of claim 1 , wherein the fluid mixture comprising at least a 1 :4 mixture of nitrogen or argon to one or more of the following: helium or neon. 9. The method of claim 1 , further comprising positioning of the substrate no more than 10mm from the outlet fluid expansion component. 10. The method of claim 9, wherein the positioning of the substrate comprises maintaining an incidence angle of about 90Â° between the substrate and the fluid expansion component. 1 1 . A method for cleaning a microelectronic substrate, comprising receiving the microelectronic substrate in a vacuum process chamber comprising a gas expansion component comprising an inlet and an outlet; positioning the substrate opposite the gas expansion component within 10mm of the outlet; 

